<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
  <title>Privacy Policy — South Bay Today</title>
  <style>
    body {
      font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', sans-serif;
      max-width: 640px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 40px 20px;
      color: #1a1a1a;
      line-height: 1.7;
      background: #faf9f6;
    }
    h1 { font-size: 24px; margin-bottom: 8px; }
    h2 { font-size: 18px; margin-top: 32px; }
    p { margin: 12px 0; color: #333; }
    .updated { color: #888; font-size: 13px; }
    a { color: #1d9bf0; }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p class="updated">Last updated: April 5, 2026</p>

  <p>South Bay Today is a community information tool for the South Bay area. We respect your privacy and keep things simple.</p>

  <h2>What we collect</h2>
  <p>We don't collect personal information. We don't use cookies for tracking. We don't run ads. We don't sell data.</p>
  <p>Basic analytics (page views, general location) are collected via Vercel Analytics to understand how the site is used. No personally identifiable information is gathered.</p>

  <h2>Social media</h2>
  <p>We maintain accounts on X, Bluesky, Threads, and Facebook. When you interact with our posts on those platforms, your interactions are governed by each platform's own privacy policy. We don't collect or store your social media data beyond what's publicly visible.</p>

  <h2>Tips and feedback</h2>
  <p>If you submit a tip or feedback through our site, the content of your message is sent to our team via webhook. We don't store your IP address or other identifying information with your submission.</p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>Questions? Email <a href="mailto:hello@southbaytoday.org">hello@southbaytoday.org</a>.</p>
</body>
</html>
